headline: S&P 500 Gains and Losses Today: Chip Stocks Jump as Foxconn Spotlights AI Demand
summary: The S&P 500 added 0.6% on Monday, Jan. 6, led by a surge in semiconductor stocks as the first full week of the new year got underway.

headline: Why Teradyne (TER) Stock Is Up Today
summary: Shares of semiconductor testing company Teradyne (NASDAQ:TER) jumped 7.2% in the afternoon session after Northland analysts upgraded the stock's rating from Market Perform (Hold) to Outperform (Buy) and raised the price target from $117 to $154. The new price target implied a potential 10% upside from where shares traded before the upgrade was announced.
